column36: Promising on AW for C Cox in 2024; absent 418 days; been gelded; stable run four
column37: Good record on AW when trained by Clive Cox, winning a 6f handicap at Kempton last August and then second over 6f here last October; sold for 32,000gns shortly after that effort and then gelded; drops to 5f on his belated return; one of four runners for Stuart Williams.

column4: Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier' Handicap (Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier)
column20: 3/1 Cherry Cobbler, 6/1 Fidelius, 7/1 Twilight Fun, 8/1 Almaty Star,  Winchurch, 10/1 Nemov,  Havana Rum, 12/1 Cressida Wildes,  Ancient Times, 16/1 Solvency,  Panelli, 20/1 Merrimack
column36: Three-time course winner; mark manageable on this year's best; often front runs
column37: Has bundles of early pace and he has three course wins on his record; two turf runs in the spring aren't the runs to judge him on and he wasn't ridden as aggressively at Lingfield when returned to AW in September; this mark in range on best form and he is one to note for market confidence.

column4: Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier' Handicap (Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier)
column20: 3/1 Cherry Cobbler, 6/1 Fidelius, 7/1 Twilight Fun, 8/1 Almaty Star,  Winchurch, 10/1 Nemov,  Havana Rum, 12/1 Cressida Wildes,  Ancient Times, 16/1 Solvency,  Panelli, 20/1 Merrimack
column36: Fluffed the start at Lingfield when last seen; dangerous mark now; revival expected
column37: C&D winner; on a dangerous mark now and he had an excuse at Lingfield when last seen, blowing the start and never able to contend; no surprise to see him bounce back with a big run.

column4: Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier' Handicap (Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier)

column37: Won twice for Alice Haynes as a 2yo; well beaten in two handicaps this year, one in Ireland and then on his stable debut two weeks ago; drops in trip with the hood experiment quickly aborted; others look safer.

column4: Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier' Handicap (Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier)

column36: Running well over 6f since May; drop in trip at this venue raises a slight doubt
column37: Readily saw off 14 rivals at Ripon in August and he has backed that up with three solid efforts; drops in trip at a track that isn't sure to suit his style of racing but this should be well run.

column4: Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier' Handicap (Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier)
column20: 3/1 Cherry Cobbler, 6/1 Fidelius, 7/1 Twilight Fun, 8/1 Almaty Star,  Winchurch, 10/1 Nemov,  Havana Rum, 12/1 Cressida Wildes,  Ancient Times, 16/1 Solvency,  Panelli, 20/1 Merrimack
column36: 5f maiden win in January; promising return to action here (6f) 7 weeks ago; more to come
column37: Made all when winning a 5f maiden at Southwell in January; absent until running a race full of promise over 6f here seven weeks ago, staying on well in the straight (recorded joint fastest and fastest sectional for the final two furlongs); this mark looks well within his range on that evidence and a well-run 5f should be fine.

column4: Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier' Handicap (Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier)

column4: Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier' Handicap (Timeform Sprint Series Qualifier)
